# [8m] Albacete: migrants and workers march under flags of the International Communist League and Comrade Norah

Author: SERVIR AL PUEBLO

Publish Time: 2023-03-12T20:38:11+00:00

Modified Time: 2023-03-12T20:38:11+00:00

Description: The revolutionaries and masses of the city of Albacete have once again dyed red women's day after weeks of work that culminated in the celebration of the mobilization of 8 ...

Images: ['[8m_23.limpio.png](https://serviralpuebloperiodico.files.wordpress.com/2023/03/8m_23.limpio.png)', '[8m_19.limpio.png](https://serviralpuebloperiodico.files.wordpress.com/2023/03/8m_19.limpio.png)', '[8m_3.limpio.png](https://serviralpuebloperiodico.files.wordpress.com/2023/03/8m_3.limpio.png)', '[img_20230305_091355.limpio.png](https://serviralpuebloperiodico.files.wordpress.com/2023/03/img_20230305_091355.limpio.png)', '[img_20230305_094659.limpio.jpg](https://serviralpuebloperiodico.files.wordpress.com/2023/03/img_20230305_094659.limpio.jpg)', '[img_20230305_100059.limpio.jpg](https://serviralpuebloperiodico.files.wordpress.com/2023/03/img_20230305_100059.limpio.jpg)', '[pict0054.limpio.png](https://serviralpuebloperiodico.files.wordpress.com/2023/03/pict0054.limpio.png)']

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/SERVIR AL PUEBLO/2023-03-12T20-38-11-00-00/8m_23.limpio.png)03/12/2023

The revolutionaries and masses of the city of Albacete have once again dyed the day of working women after weeks of work that culminated in celebration of the mobilization of March 8, in which the Albacete Committerevolutionary convened together with the association of African women a block of working women against imperialism.

Throughout the last weeks, several pamphlets and institutes have occurred, with a statement that called the organization independent of the female masses for their release, in front of the lies and the instrumentalization of the bourgeois state. This pamphlet was also unclear to the mobilization convened on March 8.

Propaganda was also made on the actions and the importance of the fight of working women in the settlement of the Peñas Highway.

Painted, posters, stickers and banners appeared in several points of the city, especially in the proletarian neighborhoods where the migrant population is concentrated in significant way.

Days before the call, in a joint day, the African women of Albacete and the Albacete Revolutionary Committee prepared the banners and cactals - in Spanish and in Wolof - who took the mobilization.

A great banner gave name to the block, in which "women against imperialism" could be read.

Women and children participated in this outdoor activity.

After this preparatory work, the same day of March, Lamovilization took place in the city of Albacete in which the African and the city of the city marched after their banner, under the flags of the International Communist League.

On the posters you could read slogans such as "Long live the struggle of women Migrants" or "proletarian women for communism."

Together with the flags of the proletariat there was a portrait of Comrade Nora, which was carried along the entire tour of the mobilization.

Dozens of people joined the block that we seemly Cantabasignas as "in the fields and in the neighborhoods proletarian feminism", "United Migrants and Ahead", "Temporara for you we fight" or "Up the Banderas of the working woman" while they waved high the flags Rojas, Las Bandas of proletarian women.This mobilization was not exempt from the police presence, with police officers who did not hesitate to identify several members of the block, as they have previously carried out in the mobilizations convened by the reflections.

Despite his attempts to intimidate the organized movement, as singing the block in unison "here you can see the strength of the committee." This is a force of the masses, and that knows that it has in front of a state that does not hesitate to enter to suppress and suffocate it.

![](Images/SERVIR AL PUEBLO/2023-03-12T20-38-11-00-00/8m_19.limpio.png)![](Images/SERVIR AL PUEBLO/2023-03-12T20-38-11-00-00/8m_3.limpio.png)![](Images/SERVIR AL PUEBLO/2023-03-12T20-38-11-00-00/img_20230305_091355.limpio.png)![](Images/SERVIR AL PUEBLO/2023-03-12T20-38-11-00-00/img_20230305_094659.limpio.jpg)![](Images/SERVIR AL PUEBLO/2023-03-12T20-38-11-00-00/img_20230305_100059.limpio.jpg)![](Images/SERVIR AL PUEBLO/2023-03-12T20-38-11-00-00/pict0054.limpio.png)Commercial

