# Address the grievances of those affected by the oil spill-NDF-Mindoro

Author: Philippine Revolution Web Central

Publish Time: 2023-03-12T97:00:00-04:00

Modified Time: 2023-03-12T05:09:23+00:00

Description: The National Democratic Front (NDF) -Mindoro joins the call of the Mindoreño people to respond to the grievances of the Oil Spill's communities due to the sinking of the MT Princess Emp

Images: ['[abs-cbn-news-photo-oil-spill-mindoro.png](https://philippinerevolution.nu/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/abs-cbn-news-photo-oil-spill-mindoro.png)']

Categories: ['Environment', 'Fisherfolks']

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Philippine Revolution Web Central/2023-03-12T97-00-00-04-00/abs-cbn-news-photo-oil-spill-mindoro.png )National Democratic Front joined(NDF)-Mindoro at the call of the people's people to immediately address the grievances of the Oilspill communities due to the sinking of the MT Princess Empress in part of Naujan, OrientalMindoro in February. According to the NDF-Mindoro, the unknown 76 barangays in nine towns affected the disaster. In addition to other towns of the provinces of the impact of the oil spill.

The MT Princess Empress has a load of 800,000 liters of industrial or black oil and continues to rise. Tragedy has devastated 26 seafood in the sea protected(marine protected area)which serves as a home of different forms of water resources. Nearly 36,000 hectares of coral reef have been dwelling in the fish. It includes 7ths and 533 hectares of mangroves in Pola town.

"This damage to nature and the livelihoods of fishermen who relies on water resources is certainly perennial," according to NDF-Mindoro. In addition, such a catastrophe is also a health risk. Black oil causes a bad odor that is dangerous when human inhale. Many residents are also complaining that the smell of oil is poisonous. Oil also fears the water sources of communities in the shore.

The NDF-Mindoro criticized the slow response of government agencies to meet the oil spill. It says, "Slow response is exacerbated ... the crisis created by the oil spill."

The Mindoreño people have also pushed for them to take action only to remove the oil floating on the shores and seasons using coconut, mug, and buckets, which could possibly affect their health.

According to the NDF-Mindoro, the people are unanimously united to assert the government's investigating and cleaning oil in the sea. They should also push to provide thousands of Mindoreño fishermen. "It is only right to develop a livelihood program for fishermen who meet their needs at a time when it is not yet possible," he said.

News Source: [https://philippinerevolution.nu/angbayan/tugunan-ang-hinaing-ng-mga-apektado-ng-oil-spill-ndf-mindoro/](https://philippinerevolution.nu/angbayan/tugunan-ang-hinaing-ng-mga-apektado-ng-oil-spill-ndf-mindoro/)

