# Child Labor, Increases in the Philippines

Author: Philippine Revolution Web Central

Publish Time: 2023-03-12T99:00:00-04:00

Modified Time: 2023-03-12T05:47:23+00:00

Description: The number of children working in the Philippines rose in 2021. At the forefront of the Philippine Statistics Authority, 4.3% or 1.37 million children, ages 5-17 years, worked in that year

Images: ['[childlabor-photo-from-rappler.jpg](https://philippinerevolution.nu/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/childlabor-photo-from-rappler.jpg)']

Categories: ['Human Rights']

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Philippine Revolution Web Central/2023-03-12T99-00-00-04-00/childlabor-photo-from-rappler.jpg )The number of children or child workers in the Philippines rose in 2021. At the forefront of the Philippine Statistics Authority, 4.3% or 1.37 million children, 5-17 years old, worked that year, higher compared to 872,333 in 2020. Of this number, 69% were considered child labor oya to those " risky ”(hazardous)work for the child. These include cases where children are forced to work because of poor, placed in areas that are harmful to their health, and work that affects their education and sufficient rest. There are 31.64 million Filipino children 5-17 years old.

Most(45.7%)The Filipino workers are on farms, farms and commercial plantations. Besides, they are also found in fisheries, mines, streets, factory and private homes.

Much is in the age of 15-17, but there are also children 5-9 over the whole period of time. The incident of the Batanguage Incorpoint in the Northern Mindanao region, followed by Central Visayas Atcaraga.

#### worst form

According to a report by the International Labor Organization released in 2022, the number of young workers in the Philippines was placed at 2.1 million in 2019, twice the PSA reported 1.046 million in the year. In the study of Ilosa Philippine statistics, 2 million of them were involved in a stern job.

This number includes more than 5,000 children 15-year-old full-ups as helpers. Such employment in young people is prohibited from the law of the reactionary government.

This number also includes children who are involved in the most evil -class analysis such as commercial sexual exploitation andpornography. In accordance with international research, the Philippines is one of the global online sexual exploitation of children(OSEC or sexual exploitation of children on the Internet). Mula 2014-2017,tumaas nang 250% ang mga kaso nito. Noong 2021, mayroong 2.8 milyong kaso sabansa na iniulat ng na OSEC, lampas doble sa 1.3 kaso na naiulat noong 2020.Karamihan sa mga "kliyente" ng OSEC ay mga dayuhang pedophile.

News Source: [https://philippinerevolution.nu/angbayan/child-labor-tumitindi-sa-pilipinas/](https://philippinerevolution.nu/angbayan/child-labor-tumitindi-sa-pilipinas/)

