<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-12T99-00-00-04-00/8M-en-CABA-2023.jpg)Since February we have been preparing and organizing throughout the country to star in unemployment and the marches that developed from north to south and east to west of our country.

A successful day starring the women's and feminist movement, we won the streets because we have a lot to say.

The economic situation is increasingly difficult for workers, Laviolence did not stop and femicides are the order of the day.

In the city of Buenos Aires the day had its epicenter in the congressman where hundreds of thousands arrived to claim under the slogan "Contesta justice there are no rights or democracy, the debt is with Les and Lastrabajadadores".

At 8hs the press conference we organized together with Lacta A, CTA T, CGT, Sipreba, UTEP, the Federal current and the CCC were developed.

The conference was held in front of courts. For the CCC, the Salazar Salazar of Independent Movement of Retilates and Pensioners of LACCC took the word. Nelba greeted the unity that reflected the table, highlighted the role of national women of women in the fight for unity and honored Aclelia Iscaro. He claimed the role of retired workers, the needs that the sector has and stated that the fight for the increase in retirement must be headed, for decent work for the children and maternal partners among other things.

In the afternoon a massive march was felt from Mayoy Avenue on July 9 to Congress.

Headed by unionized workers, social movements and popular economy. With great joy we were protagonists of this day that demonstrated the great decision to win the streets: posters made love denouncing femicides, abuses, demanding school kits, the declaration of the national emergency in violence, complaints that the debt follows siendocon . The PCR and the CCC marched in columns

[[](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-12T99-00-00-04-00/8M-en-CABA-2023-1-300x164.jpg)](http://pcr.org.ar/nota/8m-miles-en-las-calles-por-nuestros-derechos/8m-en-caba-2023-1/)#### ** Jujuy, the Morales government repressed the March 8 **As the multisectoral of women and dissidents of Jujuy denounces the political barrier assaul It will not be Morales who tries to impose it. We repudiate and call reflection to the governor and the chiefs of the police who send the women police officers(also discriminated and raped within one's own force)To face us, we have just claiming for equality and against the macho violence that we are. We lost daughters, sisters and mothers because of sexist violence, we lostdemasiado ... but we also lost fear. The streets are ours **!”**

Since the incidents, there was a broad national repudiation of this representation action, organizations and personalities and immense solidarity to women who suffered and remained in the streets without hesitation.

